  "event_preview": "The Streets of St. Petersburg is a 1.8-mile (2.897 km) temporary street circuit in downtown St. Petersburg, Florida, incorporating 14 turns across city roads and a runway section of Albert Whitted Airport. IndyCar has raced here since 2003, and in most seasons the event has served as the series opener. The Firestone Grand Prix of St. Petersburg is the first race of the 2026 NTT IndyCar Series season and the 23rd IndyCar visit to the circuit, contested over 100 laps. The all-time qualifying lap record belongs to Felix Rosenqvist, who turned a 59.2706 seconds (109.329 mph) in 2024. The fastest lap in race conditions — 1:00.6795, set by Josef Newgarden in 2024 — remains the benchmark for race pace on the Streets of St. Petersburg.",
